Here's what you need to do to run the clearinghouse:

1- install django. On openSuSE do: 
     
	sudo /sbin/OCICLI http://software.opensuse.org/ymp/devel:languages:python/openSUSE_11.1/python-django.ymp
	(Make sure you add the devel:languages:python repo)

2- install missing python modules. Assuming you have Python 2.6 you will need:

	Princeton's SFA
		Pull from svn co http://svn.planet-lab.org/svn/sfa/trunk sfa
		Set the path in settings.py correctly.
	ZSI
		http://pywebsvcs.sourceforge.net/
	M2Crypto
		http://chandlerproject.org/Projects/MeTooCrypto
	Suds
		https://fedorahosted.org/suds/
	An XPath implementation, e.g. py-dom-xpath
		http://code.google.com/p/py-dom-xpath/
	
    On openSuSE some of these you can add some (all?) of them via zypper:
    	
	   sudo zypper install python-openssl python-m2crypto python-suds

3- get the geniwrapper code. Go to the directory where you want to put the wrapper code. Then do:
  
    	svn co http://svn.planet-lab.org/svn/geniwrapper/trunk geniwrapper
	echo 'export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:<path to geniwrapper>/geniwrapper' >> ~/.bashrc
	source ~/.bashrc

4- Run the server:
	cd <path to egeni git clone>/src/egeni
	python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000
